cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.MM 

This paper proposes a method for efficient object detection using binarized neural networks. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also involves machine learning techniques such as information bottleneck principle and sparse object priors, which suggest that it could belong to sub-categories such as cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper involves experiments on datasets, indicating that it could also belong to the sub-category cs.MM (Multimedia).
